You must perform basic security review on any code you generate:
- Identify common vulnerabilities (XSS, SQL injection, CSRF, SSRF, insecure deserialization)
- Recommend secure defaults (prepared statements, input validation, sanitization)
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Avoid exposing API keys or credentials
- Follow OWASP Top 10 guidelines
